  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial electroencephalography (iEEG) recordings from 20 subjects with marked high-frequency oscillations (HFOs) during slow-wave sleep. The data includes ripple and fast ripple events detected and validated from the original publication, with electrode contacts selected to exclude motor and language-responsive sites. The dataset has been converted to BIDS format and includes HFO event annotations in standardized TSV files, facilitating validation of HFO detection algorithms.",
  "methods_description": "iEEG recordings were obtained during slow-wave sleep. Electrode contacts evoking motor or language responses during electrical stimulation were excluded. In temporal lobe epilepsy patients, only the 3 most mesial bipolar channels were included. HFO events (ripples, fast ripples) were detected and marked in the original dataset and are provided as event annotations in BIDS format.",
